## 2. Definitions

"Espalier" means the Espalier design system, including compiled JavaScript,
CSS, type declarations, custom element manifests, token manifests,
documentation, examples, icons, fonts, and related materials distributed by or
on behalf of Licensor.

"Compiled Code" means Espalier in its distributed, non-source form, including
object code, minified code, obfuscated code, generated type declarations,
generated manifests, compiled and generated CSS and CSS data files, and the
bundled icon and font assets distributed in non-source form, but excluding
Source Code.

"Source Code" means the preferred human-readable form of Espalier for making
modifications, including TypeScript source, tests, build scripts, internal
architecture records, source documentation, and related unpublished materials.

"Application" means a software application, website, internal tool, product, or
service developed by or for Licensee that incorporates or depends on Espalier.

"Developer" means an individual who directly or indirectly writes, modifies,
builds, tests, integrates, configures, or deploys an Application using Espalier.

"Order Form" means a written ordering document signed by Licensor, or accepted
through Licensor's approved purchase flow, that grants production rights and
specifies fees, term, support, scope, and any additional commercial terms.

"Evaluation Use" means internal, non-production testing, prototyping,
technical evaluation, proof-of-concept work, and procurement review.

"Production Use" means use in any Application or environment made available to
customers, employees outside the evaluation team, contractors outside the
evaluation team, partners, end users, or any revenue-generating, mission
critical, or operational workflow.

