## 4. Evaluation License

Subject to this Agreement, Licensor grants Licensee a limited, revocable,
non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable license to use the Compiled
Code solely for Evaluation Use for thirty (30) days from first access.

During Evaluation Use, Licensee may make ordinary internal technical copies and
perform ordinary installation, bundling, transpilation, minification,
tree-shaking, caching, deployment to non-production environments, and testing
steps necessary to evaluate Espalier, provided those steps remain internal, do
not expose Espalier as a standalone asset, and do not create Source Code rights.

Evaluation Use does not permit Production Use, redistribution, resale,
white-labeling, benchmarking publication, competitive analysis for building or
improving a competing product, or use to provide services to third parties.

Any Evaluation Use after the thirty (30) day evaluation period requires
Licensor's written extension or an active Order Form. Licensor may extend the
evaluation period in writing.

## 5. Production License

Production Use requires an active Order Form and payment of all applicable fees.

Subject to this Agreement and the Order Form, Licensor grants Licensee a
limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable license during the
Order Form term to:

1. install and use the Compiled Code internally by the number of Developers,
   teams, domains, products, or other units stated in the Order Form;
2. incorporate the Compiled Code into Licensee's Applications; and
3. distribute the Compiled Code only as embedded within Licensee's Applications
